# S3 Uploader cron schedule
# Install: crontab scripts/crontab
# Edit PROJ_DIR and the times below to match your installation.
#
# IMPORTANT: cron interprets these times in the SERVER'S LOCAL TIMEZONE.
# CRON_TZ is silently ignored on some Debian builds, so we encode the
# UTC-equivalent in local time directly. Update the values below if
# deploying to a server in a different timezone (or if DST shifts).
#
# Server: dune (zur2-s-d-107) — Europe/Zurich (CEST = UTC+2 in summer,
# CET = UTC+1 in winter). The yaci-store source node writes daily
# parquet at 02:00 UTC. We start the pipeline at 04:00 CEST (= 02:00
# UTC) to land right after that. During CET (winter), the same entry
# fires at 03:00 UTC — still after the source data is written, just
# 1h later than ideal; the retry polling absorbs the difference.

PROJ_DIR=/home/kartik/cardano-dune-analytics

# Daily pipeline: 04:00 CEST = 02:00 UTC (yaci writes at 02:00 UTC).
# Retries every 10 min (max 12 attempts) until step 1 finds new files.
0 4 * * * $PROJ_DIR/scripts/daily-pipeline.sh >> $PROJ_DIR/logs/cron-daily.log 2>&1

# Smart contract registry: 08:00 CEST = 06:00 UTC (independent, GitHub).
0 8 * * * $PROJ_DIR/scripts/run-exporter.sh --external smart_contract_registry >> $PROJ_DIR/logs/cron-registry.log 2>&1

# Asset data: every 2 hours (independent, Minswap API).
# `0 */2` fires at minute 0 of every even hour in local time. With
# CEST that maps to 22, 00, 02, 04, ..., 20 UTC — every 2h either way.
0 */2 * * * $PROJ_DIR/scripts/run-exporter.sh --external asset_data >> $PROJ_DIR/logs/cron-asset.log 2>&1
